      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.9;margin-bottom:20px;">
        I've spent five years in cyber security across a range of environments. I started in a
        two-person SOC handling thousands of alerts a month and ended up leading a team of five,
        delivering managed detection services, and running a multi-million-pound greenfield CNI
        programme for a major UK energy operator.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.9;margin-bottom:20px;">
        My strongest ground is the intersection of security engineering and operations. I care
        about understanding how systems are actually built, not just
        monitoring them from a distance. The CNI programme brought that into focus: deploying
        OPNsense HA firewall pairs, CIS Level 2 hardening across Linux and Windows estates,
        out-of-band management architecture, and full production handover against NCSC CAF and
        NIST CSF.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.9;margin-bottom:20px;">
        Outside of work I run an extensive homelab, a three-node Proxmox/Ceph cluster that
        mirrors the infrastructure I work with professionally. It's where I test tooling before
        it goes anywhere near a client environment, and where I dig into things
        that don't come up in the day-to-day.
      </p>
